So these are two snapshots from teh “electricity are teh 911″ city we were in recently.  Click each picture to biggify it in Flickr.

The one there at the top is suppose to be sunlight.  If you look in the street you can see that its kinda hard to tell where the street is and so you drive slowly looking down streetlights and watching for douchebags walking in the street.  This shot is taken from the condo across the street from where we live.  Here is an easier to figure out rendition.

We have so far had two blackouts and are awaiting the third.

We come down the street from where the streetlight is and go into empty Calafate looking for a cheapie, decentie place to set up our tent and stay for a night or two. We pop into an tourist agency and we are pointed towards El Estrecho (El Estroocho = The Strait) Campsite. It’s very convenient, right on the main highway and next to a gas station and tire place.
